@page "/labs/support-routines"

<h1>Support routines</h1>

<p>
    This is a very rough idea!
</p>

<p>
    As developers, we often face repetitive and monotonous tasks, particularly when supporting 
    software projects. These tasks often involve conducting various types of investigations—digging 
    through logs, databases, chats, and more. Gathering all the necessary information, analyzing 
    it, and producing meaningful results can be made significantly more efficient and comfortable
    with the support of well-designed tools.
</p>

<p>
    To start, we're experimenting with simple, basic approaches, such as processing JSON files and
    filtering them using the "sls" command, supplemented with additional file information. While
    these initial steps might not seem highly practical and implementation is very primitive, they
    serve as a foundation—a first baby step toward a more streamlined process. 
</p>

<p>
    Consolidating everything into a single Razor page could prove valuable for research, result
    reporting, and further reuse of findings. 
</p>

