        indentation and highlighting.
    </p>

    <Json Highlight=@("First") Indented=@true>
        {"Id":1,"Name":"First developer"}
        {"Id":2,"Name":"Second developer"}
    </Json>
</section>


<section>
    <h2>SlsJson</h2>

    <p>
        Simple example of <code>@typeof(DotNaut.Content.SlsJson).FullName</code> component usage with
        indentation. Such content is usually provided by "sls" command (which is a shortened form of
        Select-String cmdlet in Powershell) like <code>sls -Path some.json -Pattern some_pattern</code>.
    </p>

    <SlsJson Indented=@true>
        file.ext:64:{"Id":1,"Name":"First developer"}
        file.ext:128:{"Id":2,"Name":"Second developer"}
    </SlsJson>
</section>

